# Wildcards

Wildcards are expanded by the shell before a command is executed.

| Wildcard | Meaning                         | Example           |
| -------- | ------------------------------- | ----------------- |
| `*`      | Matches zero or more characters | `ls *.log`        |
| `?`      | Matches exactly one character   | `ls file?.txt`    |
| `[abc]`  | Match one character from a set  | `ls file[12].txt` |
| `[1-5]`  | Match a character in a range    | `ls app[1-5].log` |

### Examples

```bash
ls *.txt
ls *.log
ls app*
ls *error*
ls log?.txt
ls app[12].log
ls app[1-3].log
```

