# Path Types

## Absolute Path

Starts from the root directory.

Example:

```text
/home/hamad/linux-practice/projects
```

## Relative Path

Starts from the current directory.

Example:

```text
projects/project1
```

---

# Hidden Files

Hidden files begin with a dot (`.`).

Examples:

```text
.bashrc
.profile
.config
.ssh
```

Display hidden files:

```bash
ls -a
```

