# Safety Tips

✅ Use `pwd` before deleting files.

✅ Use `ls` before using `rm`.

✅ Verify files before deleting them.

✅ Test `find` before adding `-delete`.

✅ Use `less` for large files.

✅ Use `tail -f` for monitoring live logs.

⚠ Never run:

```bash
rm -rf /
```

or

```bash
sudo rm -rf /
```

unless you intentionally want to destroy the system.

